<subSubSection pageId="73" pageNumber="468" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="73.[785,1376,609,1036]" lastBlockId="73.[168,1375,1042,1666]" pageId="73" pageNumber="468">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[785,1033,933,958]" pageId="73" pageNumber="468">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 72 mm, tail 62 mm, ear 8 mm, hindfoot 16 mm (single individual). No specific data are available for body weight. The Lesser Forest Shrew is small. Dorsum is dark olive brown to dark sepia brown, and flanks and venter are paler dark grayish brown. Throatis paler. Hindfeet are relatively long, and feet are pale buffy brown, with blackish ankles. Tail is ¢.86% of head-body length, bicolored (dark brown above, paler below), and thin. Upper first incisor is hooked, and four unicuspids form a graded series in size from largest to smallest. Chromosomal complement has 2n = 38 and FN = 64.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
